.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-PULL" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.47" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-pull \- Resolve a tracked artifact bundle and print an rsync line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose pull [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Resolve a tracked job's artifact payload directory and print the rsync command to copy it to a laptop, with SSH connection multiplexing so an OTP login node prompts only once. Read\-only: it never copies anything, opens a connection, or contacts the scheduler.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to pull instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--into\fR \fIDIR\fR
Local destination directory shown in the rsync command (default: .).
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
No examples are documented for this command.
